This paper deals with weakly-supervised CNN segmentation, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses optimization methods for training neural networks, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of Markov random field/conditional random field regularization models, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper presents experimental results using different network architectures, which is relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) research.
